	@Override
	public View onCreateView(LayoutInflater inflater, ViewGroup container,
			Bundle savedInstanceState) {
		View view = inflater.inflate(R.layout.activity_privacy, null);
		
		
		
		TextView txt1 = (TextView) view.findViewById(R.id.textView1);
		TextView txt2 = (TextView) view.findViewById(R.id.textView2);
		TextView txt3 = (TextView) view.findViewById(R.id.textView3);
		TextView txt4 = (TextView) view.findViewById(R.id.textView4);
		TextView txt5 = (TextView) view.findViewById(R.id.textView5);
		TextView txt6 = (TextView) view.findViewById(R.id.textView6);
		TextView txt7 = (TextView) view.findViewById(R.id.textView7);
		TextView txt8 = (TextView) view.findViewById(R.id.textView8);
		TextView txt9 = (TextView) view.findViewById(R.id.textView9);
		TextView txt10 = (TextView) view.findViewById(R.id.textView10);
		TextView txt11 = (TextView) view.findViewById(R.id.textView11);
		TextView txt12 = (TextView) view.findViewById(R.id.textView12);
		TextView txt13 = (TextView) view.findViewById(R.id.textView13);
		TextView txt14 = (TextView) view.findViewById(R.id.textView14);
		TextView txt15 = (TextView) view.findViewById(R.id.textView15);
		TextView txt16 = (TextView) view.findViewById(R.id.textView16);
		TextView txt17 = (TextView) view.findViewById(R.id.textView17);
		TextView txt18 = (TextView) view.findViewById(R.id.textView18);
		TextView txt19 = (TextView) view.findViewById(R.id.textView19);
		TextView txt20 = (TextView) view.findViewById(R.id.textView20);
		TextView txt21 = (TextView) view.findViewById(R.id.textView21);
		TextView txt22 = (TextView) view.findViewById(R.id.textView22);
		TextView txt23 = (TextView) view.findViewById(R.id.textView23);
		TextView txt24 = (TextView) view.findViewById(R.id.textView24);
		TextView txt25 = (TextView) view.findViewById(R.id.textView25);
		TextView txt26 = (TextView) view.findViewById(R.id.textView26);
		TextView txt27 = (TextView) view.findViewById(R.id.textView27);
		TextView txt28 = (TextView) view.findViewById(R.id.textView28);
		TextView txt29 = (TextView) view.findViewById(R.id.textView29);
		TextView txt30 = (TextView) view.findViewById(R.id.textView30);
		TextView txt31 = (TextView) view.findViewById(R.id.textView31);
		TextView txt32 = (TextView) view.findViewById(R.id.textView32);
		txt1.setText("\nMORE HEALTH PRIVACY STATEMENT\n");
		txt2.setText("\nMORE is committed to protecting your privacy. This privacy statement applies to the data collected by MORE through MORE's website and mobile applications (the \"Apps\"). It does not apply to data collected by other online or offline MORE sites, products, or services.\n");
		txt3.setText("\nI. Introduction.\n");
		txt4.setText("\nThe Apps are a travel support service that lets you gather, edit, add to, and store, information about your health through our Apps. With the Apps, you can take your health information with you.\n");
		txt5.setText("\nII. Collection of your personal information.\n");
		txt6.setText("\nThe first time you sign in to the Apps, the Apps asks you to create a MORE account. To create a MORE account, you must eventually provide personal information such as name, date of birth, e-mail address, address, postal code, phone number, gender, and country/region. Depending on which features you use, you may be asked for additional information for that feature.\n" +
				"\nWe will use the e-mail address you provide when you create your MORE account to send you an e-mail requesting that you validate your email address, to include in sharing invitations you send through the Apps and to send you App notifications.\n" +
				"\nIf a password is used to help protect your accounts and personal information, it is your responsibility to keep your password confidential. Do not share this information with anyone. If you are sharing a computer with anyone you should always log out before leaving a site or service to protect access to your information from subsequent users.\n" +
				"\nA MORE account allows you to manage health information about yourself. You choose what information to put in your records. Examples of the types of information you can store include:\nmedications\nallergies\nhealth history\nprior surgeries\ncurrent medical conditions\n" +
				"\nSome of the information stored in the records you manage may be highly sensitive, so you need to consider carefully with whom you choose to share the information. \n");
		txt7.setText("\nIII. Sharing the information in the Apps.\n");
		txt8.setText("\nA key value of the Apps is the ability to keep track of your health information while you are traveling. You may choose with whom to share your information, and you can choose to share your information that you have entered into the Apps with other users whom you designate.\n");
		txt9.setText("\nIV. How we use your personal information.\n");
		txt10.setText("\nWe use personal information collected through the Apps, including health information, in the Apps, and as described in this privacy statement. We do not use or disclose your information except as described in this privacy statement.\n" +
				"\nIn support of these uses, MORE may use personal information:\nto provide you with important information about the Service, including critical updates and notifications;\nto send you the MORE e-mail newsletter, if you opt-in;\n" +
				"\nMORE may access and/or disclose your personal information if we believe such action is necessary to: (a) comply with the law or respond to legal process served on MORE; or (b) protect the rights or property of MORE (including the enforcement of our agreements).\n" +
				"\nMORE will not share any of your personal information in such a way that it can be used to personally identify you.\n" +
				"\nPersonal information stored in the service may be processed in the United States or any other country in which MORE or its affiliates, subsidiaries or service providers maintain facilities.\n");
		txt11.setText("\nV. How we use aggregate information and statistics.\n");
		txt12.setText("\nMORE may use aggregated information from the Service to improve the quality of the Apps and for marketing of the Apps (for example, to tell potential advertisers how many Apps users live in the United States). This aggregated MORE is not associated with any individual account. MORE does not use your individual MORE account and record information from the Apps for marketing without MORE first asking for and receiving your opt-in consent.\n");
		txt13.setText("\nVI. Service access and controls.\n");
		txt14.setText("\nYou choose whether to create an account with the Apps. The required MORE account information consists of a small amount of information such as your name, e-mail address, region, and App credentials. We may request other optional information, but we clearly indicate that such information is optional. You can review and update your account information. You can modify, add, or delete any optional MORE account information by signing into the Apps and editing your account profile.\n" +
				"\nYou can close your MORE account at any time by signing into the Apps and editing your account profile. We wait 180 days before permanently deleting your MORE account information in order to help avoid accidental or malicious removal of your information. Contact Customer Service if you want to reopen an account. Consider deletion carefully, because we may not be able to reopen it.\n" +
				"\nWhen you close your MORE account, the Apps deletes all record for which you are the sole custodian.\n");
		txt15.setText("\nVII. Deleting records.\n");
		txt16.setText("\nYou can delete any record that you are a custodian of by signing in to your MORE account and editing a record's profile. We wait 180 days before permanently deleting the record information in order to help avoid accidental or malicious removal of your information.\n");
		txt17.setText("\nVIII. Deleting information.\n");
		txt18.setText("\nWhen a person moves a piece of information to the trash, custodians may still view it there, and can restore it or delete it permanently from there at any time. \n" +
				"\nPermanently deleting information removes it from the trash. Once someone permanently deletes an item, we cannot restore it. The Service adds an entry in your record history noting the name of the person who permanently deleted information and the date the deletion occurred.\n");
		txt19.setText("\nIX. E-mail controls.\n");
		txt20.setText("\nTo keep you informed of the latest improvements, MORE may send you a newsletter. You can choose whether to receive newsletters when you sign up for the Apps, or unsubscribe at any time.\n" +
				"\nThe service will periodically send you an email summarizing recent account activity. If you do not want to receive these emails, you can unsubscribe at any time.\n");
		txt21.setText("\nX. Security of your personal information.\n");
		txt22.setText("\nMORE is committed to protecting the security of your personal information. We use a variety of security technologies and procedures to help protect your personal information from unauthorized access, use, or disclosure.  When we transmit highly confidential information (such as a credit card number or password) over the Internet, we protect it through the use of encryption, such as the Secure Socket Layer (SSL) protocol.\n");
		txt23.setText("\nXI. Enforcement of this privacy statement.\n");
		txt24.setText("\nIf you have questions regarding this statement, you should first contact us at support@more-holdings.com.\n");
		txt25.setText("\nXII. Use of cookies.\n");
		txt26.setText("\nWe use cookies with the Apps to enable you to sign in and to help personalize the Apps. A cookie is a small text file that a web page server places on your hard disk. It is not possible to use cookies to run programs or deliver viruses to your computer. A Web server assigns cookies uniquely to you and only a Web server in the domain that issued the cookie to you can read the cookies.\n" +
				"\nOne of the primary purposes of cookies is to provide a convenience feature to save you time. For example, if you personalize a Web page, or navigate within a site, a cookie helps the site to recall your specific information on subsequent visits. Using cookies simplifies the process of delivering relevant content, eases site navigation, and so on. When you return to the Web site, you can retrieve the information you previously provided, so you can easily use the site's features that you customized.\n" +
				"\nYou have the ability to accept or decline cookies. Most Web browsers automatically accept cookies, but you can usually modify your browser setting to decline some or all cookies if you prefer. If you choose to decline all cookies, you may not be able to use interactive features of this or other Web sites that depend on cookies.\n");
		txt27.setText("\nXIII. Lost or stolen information.\n");
		txt28.setText("\nYou must promptly notify us if your credit card, user name, or password is lost, stolen, or used without permission. In such an event, we will remove that credit card number, user name, or password from your account and update our records accordingly\n");
		txt29.setText("\nXIV. Changes to this privacy statement.\n");
		txt30.setText("\nWe may occasionally update this privacy statement. When we do, we will also revise the \"last updated\" date at the top of the privacy statement. For material changes to this privacy statement, we will notify you either by placing a prominent notice on the home page of the MORE Web site or by sending you a notification directly. We encourage you to review this privacy statement periodically to stay informed about how we are helping to protect the personal information we collect. Your continued use of the Apps constitutes your agreement to this privacy statement and any updates. \n");
		txt31.setText("\nXV. Contact information.\n");
		txt32.setText("\nIf you have any questions or concerns about our privacy policy, contact us at support@more-holdings.com.\n");
		
		
		return view;
	}

